    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what I found and planned:\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**4 files to touch, 1 file to create:**\n\n### Step 1 — `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`\n- Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` enum (after `Size(SizeArgs)`, line 904)\n- Add `StatsArgs` struct after `SizeArgs` (line 952) — identical shape to `SizeArgs`, same `--human/-H/--human-readable` field\n\n### Step 2 — Create `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` *(new file)*\n- Signature: `pub(crate) fn cache_stats(cache: &Cache, human_readable: bool, printer: Printer) -> Result<ExitStatus>`\n- Loop over `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 buckets; `Python` is intentionally excluded from that iterator)\n- For each bucket: `DiskUsage::new(vec![cache.bucket(bucket)]).count_ignoring_errors()` → accumulate + print `\"{bucket}: {size}\"`\n- Print `\"total: {total}\"` at the end\n- **No** `preview` parameter — this command is not experimental\n- Reuses `human_readable_bytes` (available via `use crate::commands::{ExitStatus, human_readable_bytes}`)\n\n### Step 3 — `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`\n- Add `mod cache_stats;` after `mod cache_size;` (line 84)\n- Add `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` after the `cache_size` re-export (line 21)\n\n### Step 4 — `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` right after the `CacheCommand::Size` arm (line 1181), calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)`",
